elements.name: Hydrogen
elements.description: Hydrogen is a colorless, odorless gas at room temperature. It is the lightest and most abundant element in the universe.

elements.name: Helium
elements.description: Helium is a colorless, odorless gas that is lighter than air. It is the second most abundant element in the universe.

elements.name: Lithium
elements.description: Lithium is a soft, silvery-white metal. It is the lightest metal and the least dense solid element.

elements.name: Beryllium
elements.description: Beryllium is a hard, grayish metal. It is the fourth element in the periodic table and has the atomic number 4.

elements.name: Boron
elements.description: Boron is a metalloid that is essential for plant growth. It is used in glass and ceramics.

elements.name: Carbon
elements.description: Carbon is a non-metal that is the basis of all known life. It exists in several forms, including graphite and diamond.

elements.name: Nitrogen
elements.description: Nitrogen is a colorless, odorless gas that makes up about 78% of the Earth's atmosphere.

elements.name: Oxygen
elements.description: Oxygen is a colorless, odorless gas that is essential for respiration in most living organisms.

elements.name: Neon
elements.description: Neon is a noble gas that is used in neon signs and high-voltage indicators.

elements.name: Sodium
elements.description: Sodium is a soft, silvery-white metal that reacts vigorously with water.

elements.name: Magnesium
elements.description: Magnesium is a shiny gray metal that is used in lightweight alloys and fireworks.

elements.name: Aluminum
elements.description: Aluminum is a lightweight, silvery-white metal used in a wide range of applications from packaging to aerospace.

elements.name: Silicon
elements.description: Silicon is a metalloid essential in electronics and computer chips. It is also used in construction materials.

elements.name: Phosphorus
elements.description: Phosphorus is a reactive non-metal used in fertilizers, detergents, and explosives.

elements.name: Sulfur
elements.description: Sulfur is a yellow solid non-metal used in industrial processes such as sulfuric acid production.

elements.name: Chlorine
elements.description: Chlorine is a yellow-green gas used in disinfection, plastics, and water treatment.

elements.name: Argon
elements.description: Argon is a noble gas commonly used in lighting and welding applications.

elements.name: Potassium
elements.description: Potassium is a soft metal essential for biological functions. It reacts violently with water.

elements.name: Calcium
elements.description: Calcium is a metal used in building materials and is essential for bone health in living organisms.

elements.name: Scandium
elements.description: Scandium is a soft, silvery metal often found in rare earth minerals and used in aerospace alloys.

elements.name: Titanium
elements.description: Titanium is a strong, corrosion-resistant metal used in aerospace, medical implants, and pigments.

elements.name: Vanadium
elements.description: Vanadium is a hard, silvery metal used in steel alloys to improve strength and durability.

elements.name: Chromium
elements.description: Chromium is a lustrous metal known for its high polish and used in stainless steel production.

elements.name: Manganese
elements.description: Manganese is a brittle metal essential in steelmaking and used in batteries and pigments.

elements.name: Iron
elements.description: Iron is a magnetic metal crucial in construction, tools, and the human body's oxygen transport.

elements.name: Cobalt
elements.description: Cobalt is a magnetic metal used in batteries, magnets, and to produce blue pigments in glass.

elements.name: Nickel
elements.description: Nickel is a silvery-white metal used in coins, batteries, and stainless steel.

elements.name: Copper
elements.description: Copper is a reddish metal known for its electrical conductivity, used in wiring and plumbing.

elements.name: Zinc 2
elements.description: Zinc is a bluish-silver metal used to galvanize steel, in batteries, and as a dietary supplement.

elements.name: Gallium
elements.description: Gallium is a soft metal that smells in your hands
